OL,6,FSome 42 backbenchers said the planned
OL,7,Fcuts were "impossible to support" in a
OL,8,Fletter to Sir Keir Starmer, and
OL,9,Frepresented "the biggest attack on the
OL,10,Fwelfare state since George Osborne
OL,11,Fushered in the years of austerity".
OL,13,FBut Minister Timms insisted benefits
OL,14,Fchanges would go ahead.
OL,16,F"Everybody agrees the system does need
OL,17,Freform," he said. "The system is
OL,18,Fbroken. We've got a 28 percentage
OL,19,Fpoint disability employment gap. Far
OL,20,Ftoo many people, not at the moment,
OL,21,Fgetting the opportunity for work.
